definition.value: Any form of sorbose that has D-configuration.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-(3,4-dichlorophenyl)malonamic acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A 5'-deoxyribonucleoside compound having adenosine as the nucleobase.
Any cucurbitacin whose C(23)-C(24) double bond has been reduced.
